    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-21T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-21T20:00:00-05:00" n="262"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/372a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-21T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1918—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>239. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1">Schmedeman</persName> from
                    War Trade Board:</p>
                <p>We have concluded to allow <hi rend="italic">Kim</hi> with cargo to sail and
                    Great Britain simultaneously will permit <hi rend="italic">Nobel</hi> to sail.
                    We have closed with Norwegian Government on terms our <hi rend="italic">note
                        verbale</hi> February 9,<note n="1" xml:id="d262fn1">See telegram No. 6523,
                        Feb. 9, to the Ambassador in Great Britain, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>,
                            <ref target="#pg_1127">p. 1127</ref>.</note> except increasing calcium
                    carbide to 10,000 tons and ferro silicon to 2,000 tons, and are preparing
                    agreement for signature.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
